Money Stuff =0A Here=E2=80=99s an accounting trick. You start a company. Yo=
u sell 20% of the stock to =0Ainvestors and keep 80% for yourself. The comp=
any makes widgets =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=
=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12293147&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525=
&p=3D01132025>=0A=0A=0A=0ASettlement accounting=0A=0AHere=E2=80=99s an acco=
unting trick. You start a company. You sell 20% of the stock to =0Ainvestor=
s and keep 80% for yourself. The company makes widgets; it gets $1 =0Amilli=
on of revenue from selling the widgets. The company needs raw materials to =
=0Amake the widgets. The raw materials cost $500,000. The company also has =
various =0Aother expenses =E2=80=94 salaries and rent and so forth =E2=80=
=94 which total $600,000. In =0Atotal the company has $1 million of revenue=
 and $1.1 million of expenses, for a =0Anegative net income. The economics =
aren=E2=80=99t great, and the stock won=E2=80=99t be worth =0Avery much.=0A=
=0ASo the trick is, you buy the raw materials, with your own money, and you=
 give =0Athem to the company for free. Now the company has $1 million of re=
